        <!-- Project Overview -->
        <div class="project-section">
            <h3>Project Overview</h3>
            <p>
                This project demonstrates <strong>Blue/Green deployment</strong> strategy using <strong>AWS Elastic Beanstalk</strong>, 
                enabling zero-downtime releases by maintaining two identical production environments.
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Created an <strong>Elastic Beanstalk application</strong> with load-balanced, auto-scaling environment.</li>
                <li>Deployed a sample <strong>Tomcat application</strong> to the Blue environment.</li>
                <li>Performed <strong>standard manual re-deployment</strong> with a new version.</li>
                <li><strong>Cloned the environment</strong> to create the Green environment.</li>
                <li>Deployed updated application (modified index.jsp) to Green environment.</li>
                <li>Executed <strong>URL swap</strong> to switch traffic from Blue to Green instantly.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Architecture -->
        <div class="project-section alt-bg">
            <h3>Architecture Explanation</h3>
            <p>Blue/Green deployment maintains two identical environments:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Blue Environment (Production)</strong> – Currently serving live traffic with the stable version.</li>
                <li><strong>Green Environment (Staging)</strong> – Cloned environment with the new version deployed.</li>
                <li><strong>Elastic Load Balancer</strong> – Distributes traffic to EC2 instances in the active environment.</li>
                <li><strong>Auto Scaling Group</strong> – Automatically scales instances based on demand.</li>
                <li><strong>URL Swap</strong> – Instantly switches the environment URLs, redirecting traffic to Green.</li>
                <li><strong>Rollback Capability</strong> – If issues arise, swap back to Blue environment immediately.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Implementation Steps -->
        <div class="project-section">
            <h3>Implementation Steps</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Step 1:</strong> Created Elastic Beanstalk application with "Load Balancing, Auto-scaling" environment type.</li>
                <li><strong>Step 2:</strong> Downloaded sample Tomcat application from AWS documentation.</li>
                <li><strong>Step 3:</strong> Deployed the sample app to the Blue environment (original).</li>
                <li><strong>Step 4:</strong> Used "Clone" feature to create an identical Green environment.</li>
                <li><strong>Step 5:</strong> Modified index.jsp - changed "Congratulations" to "New version".</li>
                <li><strong>Step 6:</strong> Zipped the modified application and deployed to Green environment.</li>
                <li><strong>Step 7:</strong> Performed URL swap between Blue and Green environments.</li>
                <li><strong>Step 8:</strong> Verified the original URL now shows the new version.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Key Learnings -->
        <div class="project-section alt-bg">
