                <li>Understood <strong>Blue/Green deployment</strong> pattern for zero-downtime releases.</li>
                <li>Used Elastic Beanstalk's <strong>Clone</strong> feature to duplicate environments.</li>
                <li>Performed <strong>URL swap</strong> for instant traffic switching.</li>
                <li>Learned how <strong>Load Balancer + Auto Scaling</strong> work together in Beanstalk.</li>
                <li>Practiced <strong>application versioning</strong> and deployment management.</li>
                <li>Understood the importance of <strong>rollback strategies</strong> in production deployments.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Best Practices -->
        <div class="project-section">
            <h3>Notes & Best Practices</h3>
            <p>
                Blue/Green deployment is a production-ready strategy for critical applications:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Always <strong>test the Green environment</strong> thoroughly before URL swap.</li>
                <li>Use <strong>health checks</strong> to ensure the new version is healthy.</li>
                <li>Keep the <strong>Blue environment running</strong> temporarily for quick rollback.</li>
                <li>Consider <strong>database migration strategies</strong> for schema changes.</li>
                <li>Use <strong>Route 53 weighted routing</strong> for gradual traffic shifting (Canary).</li>
                <li>Clean up old environments after successful deployment to <strong>reduce costs</strong>.</li>
                <li>Automate Blue/Green deployments using <strong>CodePipeline</strong> for CI/CD.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

